cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to develop prediction models for acute kidney injury (AKI) in critically ill patients. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves the use of supervised learning classifiers and deep learning architecture, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data-driven models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves the development of prediction models for clinical outcomes, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
